INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisher, description, startYear, numIssues, image, characters_name, concepts_name, characters_id, concepts_id, numLikes) VALUES ('2294', 'Thor', 'Whom the Gods Would Destroy!', '31', '<p>This is continued from <a href="/journey-into-mystery/4050-1497/" data-ref-id="4050-1497">Journey into Mystery (vol. 1)</a>.</p><p>Journey into Mystery volume 1 was a comic that began publication in 1952 by Atlas, and although it wasn''t until the eighty-third issue that <a href="/thor/4005-2268/" data-ref-id="4005-2268">Thor</a> even appeared in comics, let alone the title, it is most often linked to his character. This is why after releasing issue #125 of the series in 1966 that the series changed its name to become the first volume entitled Thor. As of #407, the book was renamed <a href="/the-mighty-thor/4050-61213/" data-ref-id="4050-61213">The Mighty Thor (vol. 1)</a> until #491 when it returned to simply <i>Thor</i>. In 1996, after 502 issues of the series the name changed back to <a href="/journey-into-mystery/4050-7168/" data-ref-id="4050-7168">Journey into Mystery (vol. 3)</a> which is what it was called up until its end in 1998 with issue 521. Although these later Journey into Mystery issues (#503-521) spin out of Thor vol.1, they are not counted in the collective Thor series.</p><p>In 1998, Thor''s adventures restarted with a new number one issue in <a href="/thor/4050-6226/" data-ref-id="4050-6226">Thor (vol. 2)</a> and there they were contained until issue #85 when the series concluded in 2004. After that, Thor disappeared for a couple years until he returned in 2007 for his newest volume, <a href="/thor/4050-18831/" data-ref-id="4050-18831">Thor (vol. 3)</a>, which lasted for twelve issues with its restarted numbering. Marvel then published 599 comics in the collectively-grouped "Thor" series and therefore reverted the numbering back to its original Thor with issue 600. The series again returned to it''s original title name "<a href="/journey-into-mystery/4050-39761/" data-ref-id="4050-39761">Journey Into Mystery</a>" with issue 622. And Thor continued in <a href="/the-mighty-thor/4050-39763/" data-ref-id="4050-39763">The Mighty Thor (vol. 2)</a>. With the events of <a href="/marvel-now/4015-56129/" data-ref-id="4015-56129">Marvel NOW!</a> Thor was once again restarted as <a href="/thor-god-of-thunder/4050-53920/" data-ref-id="4050-53920">Thor: God of Thunder (vol. 1)</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-the-mighty-thor-4-volume-4/4000-232239/" data-ref-id="4000-232239">Marvel Masterworks: Mighty Thor Vol. 4</a> (#126-130)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-epic-collection-when-titans-clash/4050-95441/" data-ref-id="4050-95441">Thor Epic Collection: When Titans Clash</a> (#126-130)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-vs-hercules/4050-36372/">Thor vs. Hercules</a> (#126, 221, 356 &amp; 437)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kirby-is-mighty-king-size/4050-120010/">Kirby Is... Mighty! King-Size</a> (#126, 131-133, 137-139, 160-162 &amp; 167-170)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-the-mighty-thor-5-volume-5/4000-232946/" data-ref-id="4000-232946">Marvel Masterworks: Mighty Thor Vol. 5</a> (#131-140)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-epic-collection-the-wrath-of-odin/4050-104642/" data-ref-id="4050-104642">Thor Epic Collection: The Wrath of Odin</a> (#131-153)</li><li><a href="/kingsize-kirby/4050-83141/" data-ref-id="4050-83141">King-Size Kirby </a>(#134-346 &amp; 154-157)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-kang-time-and-time-again/4050-30427/" data-ref-id="4050-30427">Avengers: Kang: Time and Time Again</a> (#140)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-the-mighty-thor-6-volume-6/4000-233357/" data-ref-id="4000-233357">Marvel Masterworks: Mighty Thor Vol. 6</a> (#141-152)</li><li><a href="http